Take photos with filter effects.

lect FILTER in the drive-mode menu.

TOYO TOY CAMERAChoose for a retro toy camera effect.
MINIATUREThe tops and bottoms of pictures are blurred for a diorama effect.
★ Pop POP COLORCreate high-contrast images with saturated colors.

DYNAMIC DYNAMIC TONEDynamic tone expression is used for a fantasy effect.
SOFT SOFT FOCUSCreate a look that is evenly soft throughout the whole image.

content.markdown:
# Filters

# Take photos with filter effects.

# 1 Press the DRIVE/DELETE button and se-
lect FILTER in the drive-mode menu.

![image](/image/placeholder)
□ 미
DRIVE
DELETE

2 Choose a filter.

| Filter | Description |
| --- | --- |
| TOYO TOY CAMERA | Choose for a retro toy camera effect. |
| MINIATURE | The tops and bottoms of pictures are blurred for a diorama effect. |
| ★ Pop POP COLOR | Create high-contrast images with saturated colors. |
| ([ ※ HIGH-KEY Hi-KEY | Create bright, low-contrast images. |
| LOW-KEY LOW-KEY | Create uniformly dark tones with few areas of emphasized highlights. |
| DYNAMIC DYNAMIC TONE | Dynamic tone expression is used for a fantasy effect. |
| SOFT SOFT FOCUS | Create a look that is evenly soft throughout the whole image. |
| PARTIAL COLOR (RED) | Areas of the image that are the selected color are recorded in that color. All other areas of the image are recorded in black-and-white. |
| PARTIAL COLOR (ORANGE) | Areas of the image that are the selected color are recorded in that color. All other areas of the image are recorded in black-and-white. |
| PARTIAL COLOR (YELLOW) | Areas of the image that are the selected color are recorded in that color. All other areas of the image are recorded in black-and-white. |
| ○ PARTIAL COLOR (GREEN) | Areas of the image that are the selected color are recorded in that color. All other areas of the image are recorded in black-and-white. |
| 48 PARTIAL COLOR (BLUE) | Areas of the image that are the selected color are recorded in that color. All other areas of the image are recorded in black-and-white. |
| PARTIAL COLOR (PURPLE) | Areas of the image that are the selected color are recorded in that color. All other areas of the image are recorded in black-and-white. |
